When black-market artifacts dealer Hamilton Finch stumbles upon a cache of ancient treasures, he does not expect to come face-to-face with Zeus himself! Is it true? Do the gods walk among us? And what event has caused them to show themselves after so many millennia? Panteon was created by celebrity actor Michael Chiklis (Fantatsic Four, The Shield)!

description: Its the deadliest game of capture the flag ever but this time, the flag is a Covenant religious leader! The Prophets are a leadership caste, and the Covenant looks to them with awe and reverence. To kill a Prophet would only increase Covenant hostilities with humanity but to capture one could lead to a truce. Enter Master Chief and the Spartans! But even with upgraded armor and new tech, can Master Chief stop a Covenant invasion armada 700 ships strong? And if the Spartans fall, will the Covenants next target be Earth? Halo: Fall of Reach Invasion continues the adaptation of Eric Nylunds novel Halo: The Fall of Reach, based on the international video game sensation Halo! description:
As Mockingbird clings to life, Hawkeye and the New Avengers go on the hunt for Superia!

Also: Spider-Woman is captured, and an old enemy is reborn!

Plus: we reveal an untold tale of Spider-Man and the Avengers!

Includes material reprinted from New Avengers #13, Avengers #12.1 and Avengers Classic #11.

Powerlord Kruun has infiltrated Utopia, and wants revenge on the X-Men - and his first targets are Kitty Pryde and Colossus!

Also: Hope and Wolverine battle a desperate killer!

By Kieron Gillen, Terry Dodson and Ibraim Roberson.

Includes material reprinted from Uncanny X-Men #537-539

A Fear Itself chapter! The Juggernaut has been transformed by the Serpent and is marching on San Francisco. The X-Men are tasked with stopping him but their old enemy is more powerful than ever!

Includes material reprinted from Uncanny X-Men #540-542.

Fear Itself tie-in! Spider-Man is rocked by the event of the year. Manhattan is gripped in violent panic. Peter Parker has not slept in days. Abandoning his friends and family, Spider-Man cannot...WILL not... stop if there are people to be saved. But as the opening salvos of Fear Itself take their violent toll, will Spidey have what it takes to fight his own doubts? Find out here!

Plus, Red Hulk is dead! Only Spider-Man stands in the way of the subterranean invasion of Manhattan.

Also, with great power, there must also come great responsibility and when those in power abuse it, its the peoples responsibility to remove them. The year is 1933, and New York City is not-so-secretly run by corrupt politicians, crooked cops, big businessesand suave gangland bosses like New Yorks worst, the Goblin. But when a fateful spider-bite gives the young rabble-rouser Peter Parker the power to fight the mobster who killed his Uncle Ben, will even that be enough? Its a tangled web of Great Depression pulp, with familiar faces like youve never seen them before.

Includes material reprinted from Fear Itself: Spider-Man #1, Avenging Spider-Man #3 and Spider-Man Noir #1.
name: Fear Itself: Day one; My friends can beat up your friends: part 3; Spider-Man Noir: part 1

description:
Daredevil is in the clutches of Klaw, master of sound! Can the man without fear defeat a creature built out of pure energy? Don't miss an amazing adventure by Mark Waid and Paolo Rivera.

Also: Avengers Academy faces one of the deadliest threats in the universe: Korvac! The Avengers fight a losing battle as the Academy students plan an astonishing attack!

By Christos Gage and Tom Raney.

Matt Murdocks new client has made some very powerful enemies can Daredevil protect him from the forces of Hydra, AIM and the Zodiac?!

Also: The Avengers Academy students have just grown up fast, thanks to some time travel manipulation! But theyre facing the one creature who has killed every Avenger hes ever fought the cosmic threat called Korvac!

Includes material reprinted from Daredevil #4-5 and Avengers Academy #12.

Wolverine needs help with a deadly Shiar battle robot, and chooses Deadpool as cannon fodder! Dont miss the craziest team-up of the year!

Also: Deadpool faces the one opponent who can overload his healing factor: THE HULK!!!

Includes material reprinted from Wolverine/Deadpool: The Decoy #1 and Deadpool #37-38.

A Fear Itself chapter! As the world falls into chaos, X-Force battle with the mutant-hating Purifiers!

Also: Deadpools less-than brilliant plan to kill himself continues, as he gets the Hulk even madder than last issue!

Includes material reprinted from Fear Itself: Uncanny X-Force #1-2 and Deadpool #39.

A desperate Doctor Octopus has a nuclear bomb aimed at New York, and he's going to use it - unless Iron Man obeys his every command!

By Matt Fraction and Salvador Larroca.

Thor and the Asgardians face a deadly crisis as the Silver Surfer arrives on Earth with a dire warning: Galactus is coming!

By Matt Fraction and Olivier Coipell.

The Falcon searches for Master Man and Sin, daughter of the Red Skull! The trial of Captain America begins as Bucky Barnes fights to clear his name!

Can Iron Man save Doc Ock's life and stop the vile villain from destroying New York?!!

By Matt Fraction and Salvador Larroca.

Plus: The Mighty Thor goes toe-to-toe with the Silver Surfer!

By Matt Fraction and Oliver Coipel.

Also: The Trial of Captain America! The new red Skull 's plan for revenge on Bucky continues, and Black Widow and Falcon are crucial to its success!

By Ed Brubaker and Butch Guice.

The Hulk and the Red She-Hulk battle a threat from ancient mythology in Rome! But is the immortal Tyrannus their ally or an even greater enemy?!

By Greg Pak and Tom Grummett.

Also: The Red Hulk is tracked by a relentless nemesis, and the mysterious creature known as Zero/One locates the killer called Black Fog!

By Jeff Parker and Gabriel Hardman.

Includes material reprinted from Incredible Hulks #627-628 and Hulk #32.

The Hulk and the Red She-Hulk take on their old enemy as the sinister Tyrannus wreaks havoc in Rome!

By Greg Pak and Tom Grummett.

Plus: The Red Hulk faces a living nightmare: the mystical serial killer called Black Fog!

By Jeff Parker and Gabriel Hardman.

Includes material reprinted from Incredible Hulks #629-630 and Hulk #33.

description: Thomas realizes that he may have bitten off more than he can chew when he agreed to become property of Genetiks. He tries to find out more about what is happening to him and ends up running to the only person he thinks he can trust. But will Alice be able to help him?

Thomas Hale's life is a lie. He has finally figured out the plan behind the Genetiks Corporation and he has more questions that answers. Everyone he knows is disappearing as if they never existed, his only hope to make it out alive might rest with Alice.

What happens to Thomas Hale when the company he works for cracks his genetic code? Genetiks is a pharmaceutical company on the cutting edge of biological science. Thomas Hale is one of thousands of employees in the Genetiks' labs. Like his colleagues, he had agreed to give a drop of blood to his employers; a drop of blood that will allow the researchers at the company he works for to decode his entire genome. As the drop of blood is the property of Genetiks, Thomas will become, in effect, the first man to be privately owned by the corporation he works for.

description: Wallace and Gromit, the beloved inventor and his faithful dog, are back with a series of all-new adventures! 8 incredible escapades await inside this fantastic collection of the Wallace & Gromit Daily Strips. Whether it's grinning and bearing it with some home dentistry, bringing in the honey with a rooftop beehive, or spicing up the local park with a robotic dinosaur, Wallace's days are filled with fun, surprises... and terrible puns!

Wallace and Gromit, the unstoppable inventor and his long-suffering dog, are back with a series of all-new adventures! 8 thrilling escapades await inside this brilliant collection of the Wallace & Gromit Daily Strips. This time around, Wallace and Gromit grapple with runaway spaghetti, sort things out with the neighbours, take time out for a beach holiday and warm up for a little friendly football! The days at West Wallaby Street are packed with fun, surprises... and terrible puns!

Wallace and Gromit, the inventor who always has a new idea, and his dog who always has to save the day, are back with a series of all-new adventures! 8 exciting tales await inside this fantastic collection of the Wallace & Gromit Daily Strips. There are jokes aplenty in this selection of fabulous funnies! Have a 'twitch' and go bird-watching with Wallace and Gromit - or join them on a trip to the zoo! How about a haircut? Wallace has the perfect tonic! And that's without mentioning the new chauffeur-driven limo service Wallace has started up... or his 'relaxing' camping trip! Wallace's weeks are filled with fun, surprises... and terrible puns!

Wallace and Gromit, the madcap inventor and his faithful dog, are back with a series of all-new stories! 8 brilliant adventures await inside this great collection of the Wallace & Gromit Daily Strips. Whether it's struggling with a no-cheese diet, cultivating the perfect conker, looking back through the family tree or finding new ways to take his breakfast, Wallace's days are filled with laughs, surprises... and terrible puns!

Wallace and Gromit, the inventor extraordinaire and his long-suffering dog, are back with a series of all-new stories! 8 brilliant adventures await inside this thrilling collection of the Wallace & Gromit Daily Strips. Whether it's taking up ice-skating, redesigning a scarecrow, entering a golfing competition, trying to create the best snowman or brewing the perfect cuppa, Wallace's days are filled with laughs, surprises... and terrible puns!

Wallace and Gromit, the man with an invention for every occasion and the dog with a solution for every invention, are back with a series of all-new stories! 8 terrific adventures await inside this fantastic collection of the Wallace & Gromit Daily Strips. Whether it's making the perfect birdhouse, taking a return trip to space to fix a satellite, finding a nocturnal cheese-thief, or modernising the local hardware store, Wallace's days are filled with laughs, surprises... and terrible puns!

Wallace and Gromit are back with more fantastic new stories from their Daily adventures! 8 unbeatable tales are wrapped up in this brilliant package of the Wallace & Gromit Daily Strips. There's laughs and thrills aplenty in this oversize helping, as Wallace and Gromit escort a priceless Easter Egg to a fair, accidentally become superheroes on their way to a fancy-dress party and grapple with cheese-flavoured amnesia!

Wallace and Gromit are back with more great new tales from their Daily adventures! 8 terrific stories are wrapped up in this brilliant package of the Wallace & Gromit Daily Strips. There's chuckles and adventures by the ton in this epic collection, as Wallace and Gromit investigate Wendolene's odd behaviour, create the most immersive cinema experience ever, take up tennis... and go mountain climbing! Plus, there's a whole lot more to discover...

Dingo is man trying to get back something that was taken from him. A box. The contents of which will make Dingo stop at nothing to get it back. It's a mystery that starts in Los Angeles and takes him to Vegas and beyond. Add in a very dangerous ex-wife, the biggest dog on the planet, and dark magic and you've got a recipe for disaster that's a mix of pulp and urban fantasy.

In this Drake Snack Cakes giveaway which continues The Incredible Hulk: Mayhem at the Mount #3 Silver Surfer investigates a disturbance coming from Latveria. Meanwhile Wolverine, Hulk, and Spider-Man have followed Jubilee's trail to Doctor Doom's castle. When the trio burst in Jubilee is strapped inside a battle suit. Silver Surfer flies in and eventually they manage to free Jubilee and escape the castle.

Note: This is the only issue in this volume. It is #4 because #3 is the aforementioned Hulk giveaway, and all four Drake Snack Cakes giveways make up the entire story.

description: This book came with the lead Galactus figurine. It features a history of Galactus in timeline format. There are key issues listed as well as plenty of art and comic panels reprinted. There is also an essay exploring his nature, another with an examination of some other cosmic-level characters and their relationship to Galactus, and a final essay with reflections by various Marvel writers.
